item.title: CVE-2022-2407|2024-08-03T00:39:07.097Z -- unknown -- wp%20phpmyadmin
item.description: The WP phpMyAdmin WordPress plugin before 5.2.0.4 does not escape some of its settings, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup)
